===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}}: a bear. Compare {{och-l|熊|bear}}. In the character, two paws are visible as a pair of 匕 and the face with the open mouth is stylized as 月.

===Etymology===
; "bear-like animal"
: Apparently an areal word of {{bor|zh|aav}} origin ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Zhang, 2019}}). Compare {{cog|khr|tr=bɔnɔi}}, {{cog|sat|tr=bana|t=Indian black bear}} & {{cog|lep|ᰠᰶᰍ|tr=să-na|t=bear}}, a loanword from Santali.

; “be able to; can; ability”
: ''{{w|Shijing}}'' rhymes point to Old Chinese *''nə'', but the forms with *''-ŋ'' are also archaic (perhaps ancient dialectal variation?).

: Possibly {{inh|zh|sit-pro|-}} (which STEDT tentatively reconstructs as {{m|sit-pro|*m-nyaŋ|t=can, be able}}): compare {{cog|bo|ནུས|t= to be able to; capable; to withstand; capacity; strength; force; power; function; energy}}, {{cog|my|နိုင်|t=can, be able to, may; master; win; prevail}}. {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} also derives {{och-l|態|apparition, bearing, manner}} from this; see also {{och-l|忍|to suffer, endure}}.

: Compare the old pre-Sino–Vietnamese loanword {{m|vi|nổi||be able to; capable}}.

